4%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617=
da42abd12a ) the space to his other tenant, Prada=E2=80=94and Prada may wan=
t to open a caf=C3=A9 of its own. Whether or not Prada is opening its own c=
af=C3=A9 is pure speculation at the
moment, but that never stopped anyone in this industry. I=E2=80=99m told by=
 a source close to John McDonald, Lure=E2=80=99s owner, that he first heard=
 the rumor in Feed Me, Emily Sundberg=E2=80=99s daily newsletter, and that =
McDonald has not been contacted by the building=E2=80=99s owner. Nothing, a=
bsolutely nothing, has been confirmed.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Still, we can speculate a bit.
Remember that the group that owns Prada also owns Italy=E2=80=99s Marchesi =
patisserie=E2=80=94maker of chocolates, cookies, and yes, panettone. They h=
ave multiple locations in Milan. Would it make sense for Prada to open a ca=
f=C3=A9 in that building? Sure: The SoHo location is one of its most visite=
d stores in the world. Is it a bummer that Lure may be forced to close or m=
ove, a costly and potentially business-ruining endeavor? Yes. McDonald, the=
 former publisher of City magazine (remember it?),
has played a big role in shaping the culture of the neighborhood over the p=
ast 30 years. Preston Clark, the chef, is Manhattan food royalty. (His dad,=
 the late Patrick Clark, made his name at Odeon and Cafe Luxembourg.) It wo=
uld be sad to see it relocate from that cozy, reliable outpost.=C2=A0

That said, Lure was able to thrive in SoHo because stores like Prada existe=
d. And more
symbiosis between hospitality and fashion businesses is simply the latest e=
volution of the luxury market. (Louis Vuitton just opened a caf=C3=A9 uptow=
n; Gucci has partnered with Italy=E2=80=99s most famous chef, Massimo Bottu=
ra, on restaurants; Moncler=E2=80=99s Remo Ruffini co-owns everyone=E2=80=
=99s favorite Milan spot, Langosteria.) In the end, I=E2=80=99m a fan of re=
staurant diversity, and have always enjoyed Lure, where there=E2=80=99s lot=
s of wood paneling and wine being served at
lunch, not to mention totally acceptable sushi rolls. Here=E2=80=99s hoping=
 they can all work it out.

