Anderson: I love Allerton=E2=80=99s character [in Queer]. It was played by =
Drew, and he=E2=80=99s wearing these translucent shirts. I think for me, it=
 was a way to bridge the idea of the reality and the
nonreality=E2=80=94this idea of the translucency through to the body, the c=
igarette pack inside the pocket, and the flesh underneath. It=E2=80=99s ref=
erring to the morphing that=E2=80=99s in the book. It was like trickery wit=
hout special effects.

=E2=80=8A

What I=E2=80=99m Reading=E2=80=A6 And Listening To=E2=80=A6
-----------------------------------------

LVMH=E2=80=99s stock might be down 13 percent this year, but
Bernard Arnault and his family still topped Forbes=E2=80=99s end-of-year Bi=
llionaires List, with an estimated net worth of $233 billion, up from $211 =
billion in 2023. Boy, did I hit the jackpot when I decided to cover fashion=
-as-a-business all the way back in 2006. [Forbes ( https://www.forbes.com/b=
illionaires/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm=
_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F26%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_a=
ction&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )]

=C2=A0

Another
Arnault deputy threw a goodbye party for himself. Mo=C3=ABt Hennessy global=
 distribution head Jean-Marc Lacave, who joined the business in 2001, bid a=
dieu on December 16 with a =E2=80=9Csumptuous=E2=80=9D party on the top-flo=
or lounge of the wine-and-spirits division=E2=80=99s headquarters. Lacave a=
nd his C.E.O., Philippe Schaus, are exiting the business as middle-child Al=
exandre and Jean-Jacques Guiony
swoop in ( https://puck.news/alexandre-arnaults-promotion-lvmh-succession/?=
utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLi=
ne+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F26%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_sou=
rce=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) as co-C.E.O.s of the stru=
ggling division. [La Lettre ( https://www.lalettre.fr/fr/entreprises_luxe-e=
t-conso/2024/12/23/l-ultime-tournee-de-jean-marc-lacave-aux-frais-de-moet-h=
ennessy%2C110354937-eve?cxt=3DPUB&utm_source=3DLLA&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_c=
ampaign=3DAUTO_EDIT_SOM_PROS&did=3D110337114&utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SU=
BSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2=
F26%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df=
6c60617da42abd12a )]

=C2=A0

I cannot think of one fashion publicist capable of engaging in the type of =
warfare between all these flacks mixed up in the Blake Lively-Justin Baldon=
i drama. (Okay, maybe one.) Puck=E2=80=99s legal correspondent, Eriq Gardne=
r, breaks down what is arguably the most compelling battle here: between St=
ephanie Jones and her former
employee, Jennifer Abel. [Puck ( https://puck.news/blake-lively-vs-justin-b=
aldoni-vs-stephanie-jones-the-next-steps/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSC=
RIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F26=
%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c6=
0617da42abd12a )]

=C2=A0

If you=E2=80=99re interested in exploring the generational divide between p=
eople who look good in chinos, people who are comfortable discussing Luigi =
Mangione=E2=80=99s fashion choices and online dating presence,
and people who have read Glamorama ( https://fave.co/4gyJWjK?utm_campaign=
=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+S=
UBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F26%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustom=
er.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), be sure to check out this A-plus con=
versation between Mel Ottenberg, Chris Black, and Jason Stewart. [How Long =
Gone ( https://howlonggone.com/734-mel-ottenberg?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+=
-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%28=
12%2F26%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=
=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )]

=C2=A0

Two more podcasts for
my particular breed of dork: One is an oral history of Mars Incorporated, m=
aker of M&Ms, Snickers, and Kind Bars. It=E2=80=99s a private company and g=
enerates $50 billion a year in sales=E2=80=94more than Coca-Cola! (Although=
, now that soda is trending again=E2=80=A6 maybe not for long.) The other i=
s an interview with the creators of Fast Company, founded in 1995, just as =
older millennials were entering their teens. The launch of Fast Company con=
verges with the end of the concept of selling out, and
you=E2=80=99ll understand why after listening to this. [Acquired ( https://=
www.acquired.fm/episodes/mars-inc-the-chocolate-story?utm_campaign=3DLine+S=
heet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBER=
S+%2812%2F26%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm=
_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) and This Podcast Should Really Start Advertisi=
ng With Us, Given How Much I Promote It ( https://podcasts.apple.com/us/pod=
cast/alan-webber-bill-taylor-founders-fast-company/id1617198343?i=3D1000681=
795033&utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F30%2F24%29&utm_conte=
nt=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2812%2F26%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&=
utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )]

=E2=80=8A

And finally=E2=80=A6 My 2025 resolution is to uncross my legs, and
not just at fashion shows.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Happy New Year and see you Thursday,

Lauren

