ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Any intel or thoughts on the Prada-Lure
situation?</strong>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I have <em>so many thoughts=
</em>, but to summarize: Lure Fishbar, the basement restaurant on the corne=
r of Mercer and Prince, might have to close <em>at some point </em>because =
<strong>Peter Brant</strong>, the <strong>Warhol </strong>benefactor and pa=
per magnate <em>and </em>owner of the building,
is rumored to be <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImR=
nVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVR2RvTW54YzZCTDEyaUczSG9ITT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly=
9ueS5lYXRlci5jb20vMjAyNC8xMi8xNy8yNDMyMjgxMC9sdXJlLWZpc2hiYXItY2xvc2luZy1wc=
mFkYS1yZXN0YXVyYW50LXJ1bW9ycz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249TGluZStTaGVldCstK1NVQlNDUklC=
RVJTKyUyODEyJTJGMzAlMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PUxpbmUrU2hlZXQrLStTVUJ=
TQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMiUyRjI2JTJGMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvbl=
x1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhY=
mQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwMjM2OTh9=
/3a1a9be57d35ecb3d697c2ec834d37f8fc2f9ba179ea5b1223e02ce4c07c7a41" style=3D=
"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">selling</a> the space to his <em=
>other</em> tenant, Prada=E2=80=94and Prada may want to open a caf=C3=A9 of=
 its own. Whether or not Prada is opening its own caf=C3=A9 is <em>pure</em=
> speculation at the
moment, but that never stopped anyone in this industry. I=E2=80=99m told by=
 a source close to <strong>John</strong> <strong>McDonald</strong>, Lure=E2=
=80=99s owner, that he first heard the rumor in Feed Me, <strong>Emily Sund=
berg</strong>=E2=80=99s daily newsletter, and that McDonald has not been co=
ntacted by the building=E2=80=99s owner. Nothing, absolutely <em>nothing</e=
m>, has been confirmed.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Still, we can speculate =
a bit.
Remember that the group that owns Prada <em>also</em> owns Italy=E2=80=99s =
Marchesi patisserie=E2=80=94maker of chocolates, cookies, and yes, panetton=
e. They have multiple locations in Milan. Would it make sense for Prada to =
open a caf=C3=A9 in that building? Sure: The SoHo location is one of its mo=
st visited stores in the world. Is it a bummer that Lure may be forced to c=
lose or move, a costly and potentially business-ruining endeavor? Yes. McDo=
nald, the former publisher of <em>City </em>magazine (remember it?),
has played a big role in shaping the culture of the neighborhood over the p=
ast 30 years. <strong>Preston</strong> <strong>Clark</strong>, the chef, is=
 Manhattan food royalty. (His dad, the late <strong>Patrick</strong> <stron=
g>Clark</strong>, made his name at Odeon <em>and</em> Cafe Luxembourg.) It =
would be sad to see it relocate from that cozy, reliable outpost.=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>That said, Lure was able to thrive in SoHo <em>=
because</em> stores like Prada existed. And more
symbiosis between hospitality and fashion businesses is simply the latest e=
volution of the luxury market. (Louis Vuitton just opened a caf=C3=A9 uptow=
n; Gucci has partnered with Italy=E2=80=99s most famous chef, <strong>Massi=
mo</strong> <strong>Bottura</strong>, on restaurants; Moncler=E2=80=99s<str=
ong> Remo Ruffini</strong> co-owns everyone=E2=80=99s favorite Milan spot, =
Langosteria.) In the end, I=E2=80=99m a fan of restaurant diversity, and ha=
ve always enjoyed Lure, where there=E2=80=99s lots of wood paneling and win=
e being served at
lunch, not to mention totally acceptable sushi rolls. Here=E2=80=99s hoping=
 they can all work it out.</p></div>
